Parliament, Friday, 1 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Environmental Affairs will on Monday hold an inquiry into the alleged closing off of the Clifton 4th Beach to the members of the public on 23 December last year. The committee has invited stakeholders such as the Department of Environmental Affairs, City of Cape Town, the Professional Protection Alternatives (PPA) Security company, South African Police Service (SAPS); Private Security Industry Regulatory Authority (PSIRA) and the affected people. When this incident happened in December last year, the Chairperson of the committee, Mr Phillemon Mapulane condemned the incident and assured everyone that there will be a meeting in the new year with all the stakeholders involved to ascertain what led to this incident. Committee Meeting details: Date: Monday, 4 February 2019
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ENVIRONMENTAL AFFAIRS, MR PHILLEMON MAPULANE. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Faith Ndenze (Ms)
